President Obama issued a statement on the departure of Solicitor General Don Verrilli, praising his five years of service fighting for a better future in the highest court. Verrilli's efforts resulted in landmark cases that moved America forward, such as ensuring quality and affordable healthcare for 20 million more Americans, combating discrimination for women and minorities, reaffirming fair treatment for immigrants, and allowing freedom to marry for all. President Obama expressed gratitude for Verrilli's counsel and friendship and wished him and his family the best in their future endeavors, including a well-deserved vacation.